Certainly! Here's a LaTeX table summarizing the sentence in two rows:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{array}
\begin{document}

\begin{table}[h!]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{|m{5cm}|}
\hline
The movie was interesting. \\ \hline
Too many plot twists. \\ \hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\end{document}
```

This table captures the essence of the sentence in two concise rows.
